		<!-- message -->
		<div><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<i>Originally posted by Slashem </i><br />
<b>I'm sure everyone's gonna have some input on this.<br />
<br />
I'm the main tank for the guild. As standard, I engage mob first to build up aggro then call in the troops. Problem is that they move the mob all over the place. I realise that this will be a VERY big problem in the future when we have AE mobs and have to keep the casters out of range and using ER3 items to hit the mob.<br />
<br />
I have the standard more left, more back, more front more right commands hotkeyed to spam raidchannel. Problem is everyone shifts that way then mobs is still getting moved around.<br />
<br />
How do you handle this? I've got a few guys that get the concept, but dammit there's just a few dumb brutes out there that consistently can't handle that idea.<br />
<br />
Do I assign ppl that move?<br />
<br />
Then there's the ppl that jump in front of you, blocking your line of sight, and eventually you can't hit the mob due to the rat pack surrounding him.<br />
<br />
very...very...very...frustrating </b>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div><br />
You need to make it very clear to people that the mob needs to be surrounded so that it doesn't get pushed into casters, too far out of camp, up trees/walls etc. Try things like &quot;a few go to the right&quot;. If too many go, say &quot;too many&quot; etc. It does take other people a little practice to learn how many chars on one side is too many.<br />
<br />
If too many people are behind the mob, after it gets pushed a certain distance you can switch sides with all the people behind it and push it back the other way... when it goes back too far, switch sides again, etc. We call this walk tanking.<br />
<br />
People really need to cooperate on raids. If you're explaining what to do and everything over raidchat and some people still aren't getting it, start calling out offenders by name over raid channel or send them tells and tell them what they're doing wrong.  <br />
<br />
Make it a very strong point that absolutely nobody steps in front of the MT either. Call out people who do this immediately.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
