				<div class="info">   </div>
				</div>														
		
	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>There is no way to keep a mob stationary if you have 2 or more people attacking. Sure, in theory you COULD keep a mob very near a single points, but the chances of that are slim. No matter what you tell your guild, you will always have idiots attacking on the front side, pets pushing from the wrong direction, and casters who don't understand how to control the direction their spells push.<br />
<br />
Pick any 10 uber guild web sites and look for corpse shots of mobs that do not have a handy corner. You'll find 9/10 mobs on top of pillars, walls, fire pots, trees, or just about any other game geometry you can think of. I think every guild has a running joke about their l33t mob positioning abilities. I know my guild has 250 skill in getting a mob to a retarded place.<br />
<br />
Pet swarms are also uber positioning tools. Nothing like 60 mini pets pushing the mob all over the zone.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
