		<!-- message -->
		<div>The way we do in in my guild is:<br />
<br />
-Easy named's/Regular mobs:MT alone in front, rogues in back rest spraid on the sides<br />
Mobs dont move much that way.<br />
<br />
-Long hard named's everone in the back and MT walks back then calls the turn and everyone turns around and push mob back the other way.<br />
<br />
Another good way to help MT keep mob relatively stedy is to put the pets in front of mob with MT. They sure might die and do less dmg but they push a lot too so mob will stay more in one spot.<br />
<br />
It all depends on the situation though. Cornering the mob is probably the best way to tank it. But yet again you cannot corner them all, sadly.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
